      "writtenOn": "2021-06-21T21:57:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree that this will break up the render pass in the case that is both msaa_render_to_texture and no barrier support. But I think the problem is that we might STILL need a barrier before sampling that texture, even though we broke up the render pass. We\u0027re still reading from and writing to the same texture after all, and in GL there isn\u0027t a notion of render passes, so I don\u0027t know how else the driver would know it needs to flush that texture so we can sample it.\n\nEither way though we definitely need to check whether we are a texture proxy before taking this branch.",
      "parentUuid": "887db8f5_d57523da",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 2034,
        "startChar": 9,
        "endLine": 2034,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "8df97f74dc70f66de7fb9de799f37adc34748b41",
